'''Juan Camilo Portilla Orozco''' (born 12 September 1998) is a Colombian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Club Athletico Paranaense|Athletico Paranaense]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

After beginning his career in Colombia with youth sides including [[Boca Juniors de Cali|Boca Juniors Cali]] and breaking into senior football with Universitario Popayán, he had stints abroad at [[Jacksonville Armada]] in the United States and [[Deportes Melipilla]] in Chile, before returning to Colombia with [[Alianza Petrolera]]. In 2022, he joined [[América de Cali]] on loan and later made the move permanent in 2023. In 2024, he signed for Argentine club [[Talleres de Córdoba|Talleres]].

Portilla was first called up to the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] national team in 2023 and made his senior debut in 2024 during a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].

==Career==
Portilla began his career with [[Boca Juniors de Cali]] at youth level, then the youth ranks of [[Universitario Popayán]]. In 2016, he made his professional debut with Universitario Popayán in the [[Categoría Primera B|Colombian second level]].<ref name="of">{{cite web |title=Conociendo a Juan Camilo Portilla: el caleño más americano |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/conociendo-a-juan-camilo-portilla-el-caleno-mas-americano-38186319 |website=OneFootball |access-date=4 October 2024 |language=es |date=4 October 2024}}</ref>

In 2018, Portilla emigrated to the United States and joined [[Jacksonville Armada FC|Jacksonville Armada]].<ref name="ja">{{cite instagram |user=jaxarmadafc |postid=C_ypW5OB2YW |title=Congratulations to former Jacksonville Armada FC midfielder Juan Portilla (@laporti10) on making his debut for @fcfseleccioncol! 🇨🇴 |date=11 September 2024 |access-date=4 October 2024}}</ref> In the second half of the same year, he moved to Chile and played for [[Deportes Melipilla]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Con un ex Melipilla incluido: La nómina de Colombia para enfrentar a Chile por Clasificatorias |url=https://www.emol.com/noticias/Deportes/2024/10/04/1144554/nomina-seleccion-colombia-chile-clasicatorias.html |website=Emol |publisher=[[El Mercurio]] |access-date=4 October 2024 |language=es |date=4 October 2024}}</ref>

Back to Colombia, Portilla played for [[Alianza Petrolera F.C.|Alianza Petrolera]] and [[América de Cali]] in the top level.<ref>{{cite news |title=Juan Camilo Portilla: "Mi idea es jugar en Europa, ojalá en Italia" |url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/juan-camilo-portilla-mi-idea-es-jugar-en-europa-ojala-en-italia-35788927 |access-date=4 October 2024 |work=OneFootball |date=4 October 2024 |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=América alista compra y renovación: noticia que gustará a los hinchas |url=https://www.futbolred.com/futbol-colombiano/liga-betplay/juan-camilo-portilla-seria-comprado-por-america-de-cali-y-renovado-hasta-2025-165125 |access-date=4 October 2024 |work=futbolred.com |date=4 September 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

In 2024, Portilla signed with Argentine club [[Talleres de Córdoba]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sanguedolce |first1=José |title=Juan Camilo Portilla Orozco es nuevo refuerzo de Talleres |url=https://www.clubtalleres.com.ar/juan-camilo-portilla-orozco-es-nuevo-refuerzo-de-talleres/ |access-date=4 October 2024 |work=Club Atlético Talleres |date=5 January 2024 |language=es}}</ref>

==International career==
At youth level, Portilla represented the [[Colombia national under-15 football team|Colombia under-15 national team]].<ref name="of"/>

Portilla received his first call up to the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia senior team]] for the [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] on 18 January 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=Juan Camilo Portilla y su primera convocatoria con la Selección Colombia |url=https://onefootball.com/id/berita/juan-camilo-portilla-y-su-primera-convocatoria-con-la-seleccion-colombia-36620884 |website=OneFootball |access-date=4 October 2024 |language=es |date=18 January 2023}}</ref> He made his debut in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] on 10 September 2024.<ref name="ja"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Rojas Aldana |first1=Daniela |title=Colombia triunfa ante Argentina con James Rodríguez como estrella |url=https://www.vavel.com/colombia/futbol-colombiano/2024/09/11/1195851-colombia-triunfa-ante-argentina-con-james-rodriguez-como-estrella.html |access-date=4 October 2024 |work=VAVEL |date=11 September 2024 |language=es |quote=James, fue sustituido sobre los 90 minutos en medio de aplausos por Juan Camilo Portilla, quien hizo su debut con la selección.}}</ref>

